# Railway File Uploader – CRUD with PostgreSQL

[![Flask](https://img.shields.io/badge/Flask-2.3-blue)](https://flask.palletsprojects.com/)
[![PostgreSQL](https://img.shields.io/badge/PostgreSQL-15-336791)](https://www.postgresql.org/)
[![Railway](https://img.shields.io/badge/Railway-deployed-0B0D0E)](https://railway.app/)

A production‑ready file management system deployed on **Railway**.  
Users can **upload**, **list**, **rename**, **download** and **delete** files.  
File metadata is stored in a **Railway‑managed PostgreSQL** database, while file contents are persisted on a **Railway Volume** (ephemeral‑safe storage).  
Full CRUD operations, automatic logging, and easy horizontal scaling (with object storage) are documented.

---

## ✨ Features

- 📤 **Upload** any file (with size limit)
- 📋 **List** all uploaded files with metadata (name, size, upload date)
- ✏️ **Rename** existing files (updates both filename and DB)
- ⬇️ **Download** files directly
- 🗑️ **Delete** files (removes from disk and DB)
- 🗄️ **PostgreSQL** stores all file metadata
- 💾 **Railway Volume** for persistent file storage
- 🚀 **One‑click deploy** on Railway (auto‑deploy from GitHub)
- 📊 **Structured logging** to stdout (collected by Railway)
- 🔧 **Environment variable** configuration

---

## 🧱 Tech Stack

| Layer       | Technology                         |
|-------------|------------------------------------|
| Backend     | Python 3.10+ / Flask               |
| Database    | PostgreSQL 15 (Railway managed)    |
| File Store  | Local filesystem (Railway Volume)  |
| Deployment  | Railway (with Procfile + Gunicorn) |
| Logging     | Python `logging` → stdout          |
| CI/CD       | GitHub → Railway automatic deploys |

---

## 📋 Prerequisites

- [Python 3.10+](https://www.python.org/)
- [PostgreSQL](https://www.postgresql.org/) (for local testing)
- [Railway account](https://railway.app/) (for deployment)
- `git` and a GitHub repository

---

